Lappie Labuschagne said that he went to the bank after noticing that R84 was being deducted from his bank account.He managed to stop the debit order and later found out that it was a technical glitch .Mr Labuschagne said that he knows about 43 of his fellow colleagues who had the same problem.They have all since managed to get their money back. Pensioners should have a look at their accounts and see if the same thing happened to them. If it does, they must go to their bank to sort it out, Mr Labuschagne advises.